cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with self-supervised learning in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image-related regression problems such as image quality assessment and crowd counting. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an efficient backpropagation technique for Siamese networks, which is related to optimization and training of neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of ranking as a proxy task for regression problems also involves concepts from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the application of the proposed framework to image-related problems suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant category.
